
-------------------------------------------------------------------------

Version Control Software:

-------------------------------------------------------------------------

git add
	add files

git branch 
	see branch

git checkout branch-name
	checkout

git clean
	Removes untracked files

git clone
	clone new repo

git commit -m "message"
	commit changes

git commit --amend
	change recent files

git fetch
	Fetching a branch from another repository, doesn't integrate into your local repository directly

git init
	initialze new repo

git log
	see previous history

git merge
	A powerful way to integrate changes from divergent branches

git pull
	pull changes from online

git push origin branch
	push code 

git rebase
	Rebasing lets you move branches around, which helps you avoid unnecessary merge commits

git reflog
	Git keeps track of updates to the tip of branches using a mechanism called reflog

git remote
	A convenient tool for administering remote connections

git reset
	Undoes changes to files

git revert
	Undo a commit

git status
	check status

git stash
	enables you to switch branches without committing the current branch

git ignore
	used to specify intentionally untracked

git rm
	remove files

git diff
	see difference

-------------------------------------------------------------------------